                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4306: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-04-25T17:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 25, 1922—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 25—10:54 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>167. My 164 paragraph 5. Counsellor Japanese Legation called afternoon 24th and
                    expressed gratification at conferences held here and in British Legation of
                    which he had sent report to Tokyo. His Government instructed him to state to me
                    and other conferees its policy was one of no interference coupled with such free
                    and frank exchange of views and concerted action.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
